<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>DDB0118</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Alison Sharman – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Deregulation Bill</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> – Rights of way</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Many green lanes in national parks – areas set aside for peaceful recreation – have for many years been threatened by serious damage caused by unregulated use of recreational 4x4 and trail bikes.  These vehicles rut up the ground and are a nuisance to other park users through noise and pollution.  Unsealed surfaces cannot withstand modern transport and I have witnessed many lanes that have been destroyed beyond repair by motorised recreational vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I would like the Deregulation Bill to enable the protection of unsealed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(i.e. not surfaced with tarmac) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">green lanes in national parks by including a clause: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 27pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">All unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATs), and all unsealed Unclassified County Roads (UCRs) should be recognised as NOT being part of the ordinary roads network, and should be re-classified as Restricted Byways.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This clause will effectively allow motorised vehicles that need access to premises (farm vehicles etc.)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,  along</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with pedestrians, horses, horse-drawn carriages and cyclists to travel along green lanes, but prevent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> access to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> recreational vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In addition, I wish to see a further clause to give local communities greater influence to determine the management of green lanes in their areas: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 27pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">When a local authority declines to impose a traffic regulation order that is widely-supported by the public, there should be a right of appeal, either to an independent inspector, or a magistrate. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I am a member of the Yorkshire Dales Green Lanes Alliance (YDGLA) and support the formal submissions made by them to this enquiry, along with those of the Green Lanes Environmental Action Group (GLEAM), the Green Lanes Protection Group (GLPG) and the Peak District Green Lanes Alliance (PDGLA).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">15 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>